On 21 May, the British Fashion Council officially announced the final selected designers for ‘NEWGEN’ 2026/27, who are set to lead the next generation of the fashion industry.
Launched in 1993, NEWGEN is the BFC’s support programme for emerging designers, created to discover and nurture world-leading design talent. In the past, designers such as Alexander McQueen, Jonathan Anderson, and Simone Rocha have gone through the programme and grown into globally renowned designers.
A total of 16 designers were selected for this year’s programme. It will be exciting to see how these next-generation designers shape the future of the London fashion scene.
