From early stock trades to billion-dollar developments, Abbas Sajwani built one of Dubai’s fastest-growing ultra-luxury real estate companies before turning 27.
Through AHS Group and AHS Properties, he transformed early conviction into a $1.9 billion net worth. In 2026, Forbes named him the youngest real estate billionaire globally and the youngest Arab billionaire. The milestones are public. The discipline behind them rarely is.
